# Offer of Internship — AI Intern

Date: [Offer Date]

Dear Candidate,

We are pleased to offer you a fixed-term internship with Omninuera for the position of AI Intern under the terms set out below. This document is an HR draft for review and is intended to be provided to the candidate; it will be sent to Legal for review prior to finalization.

Position and Term
- Position: AI Intern.
- Duration: 3 months (fixed-term internship).
- Start Date: [Start Date].
- Reporting to: [Manager Name], [Title].

Work Arrangement and Location
- Work arrangement: Completely remote (remote-first).
- Candidate city (for record): Bengaluru.
- Location clause: This internship is fully remote. Candidate will be based in Bengaluru and must comply with applicable local laws.

Stipend and Payment
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.
- Payment schedule: The stipend will be paid monthly and will be disbursed within the first week of the following month. All payments are subject to applicable statutory deductions.

Internship Status
- The internship is a fixed-term, training-oriented engagement and does not constitute employment. It does not confer rights to employment benefits (such as paid leave, insurance, provident fund, or other employee benefits) unless expressly provided in writing by Omninuera.

Confidentiality
- During the internship and thereafter, the Candidate must maintain the confidentiality of Omninuera’s confidential and proprietary information and may not disclose such information to any third party except as authorized in writing by Omninuera. Confidential information includes, but is not limited to, technical data, business plans, product roadmaps, customer information, source code, models, training data, and other proprietary materials.

Intellectual Property
- All inventions, discoveries, developments, designs, code, models, documentation, and other work product (collectively, “IP”) that the Candidate creates or contributes to during the internship, whether alone or jointly with others, and whether or not created during normal working hours, shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera. The Candidate hereby assigns and agrees to assign to Omninuera all right, title, and interest in such IP and agrees to execute any documents reasonably necessary to effectuate this assignment.

Termination and Notice
- Termination for convenience: Either party may terminate this internship for convenience by providing seven (7) calendar days’ written notice to the other party.
- Termination for cause: Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for material breach of this offer, misconduct, violation of company policies, or other serious grounds. In the event of termination, stipend will be pro-rated to the last day worked and paid in accordance with the payment schedule, subject to applicable deductions.
- Any early termination will be handled in accordance with Omninuera’s standard exit procedures.

Compliance with Company Policies
- The Candidate must comply with Omninuera’s policies and procedures, including those relating to confidentiality, information security, acceptable use, and workplace conduct. Omninuera may update its policies from time to time.

Background Verification
- This offer is contingent on satisfactory background verification (education, employment history, and any other checks deemed appropriate by Omninuera). Omninuera reserves the right to withdraw the offer if verification is unsatisfactory.

Tax and Deductions
- The stipend is subject to all applicable taxes and statutory deductions under Indian law or other applicable jurisdictions. The Candidate is responsible for any personal tax liabilities arising from receipt of the stipend.

No Guarantee of Employment
- Completion of the internship does not guarantee an offer of employment. Any offer of employment following the internship will be subject to a separate agreement.

Acceptance Instructions
To accept this offer, please sign and return a scanned copy of this letter or send an email confirmation to HR at [HR Email Address] by no later than seven (7) calendar days from the date of this offer ([Acceptance Deadline: date to be inserted by HR]). Acceptance should include the Candidate’s printed name and signature and confirmation of the Start Date.

Company Signature (for Omninuera)

